	   <tr><td colspan=2>Simple solution... tell them to go alpha loot order. if they refuse you leave... right in the middle of a important pull by gating out.<br><br>It is completely within the rules of the game for you to do it, and while GM's won't be happy if they get petitioned by the group you left, nor will they interfere when they find out why.<br><br>Remember clerics are RARE, especially on the high end, so even if those people whine about you (like they bitch in ooc or something) simply explain back calmly why you did it and how you warned them. Trust me, the good people will understand and value you, and respect the fact you stood up for yourself.<br><br>However double edge sword here... ALWAYS GIVE THE GROUP THE CHANCE TO MEND WAYS... ask them once, then twice, to respect your loot. Using the above tactic simply because you fairly lost a loot roll or your mad the switch item in an alpha loot (remember derv 2 way back when? alpha till bronze? bronze was the switch item) is a horrible way to give all of us a bad name.<br><br>As a less severe solution, leave when your the only healer free in the zone. This is VERY useful on the high end past 34. at 34 you get superior healing... no other class gets it till 53. Leave the group between fights but when no other clerics are around. It will mess up their dynamic and slow they're pulling or raiding. Likely they will have to disband or leave.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
