	   <tr><td colspan=2>When someone demands a spell that costs so much and don't offer to donate at all, you just have to say no. I know I am only lvl 8, but I have some higher lvl cleric friends, some in my guild, who have to tell ppl no all the time. It may cause some harassment. If it gets too bad, just report them or threaten to... maybe they will stop. Ppl need to learn that you can't just take take take and expect never to give... don't feel bad about saying no to them. As for the looting problem, I have found myself leaving a group recently cuz I asked for loot and got nothing. However, the only POSSIBLE solution I could find was asking before I joined what the loot order was. If there wasn't one already set, ask that there be one. Tell them of your concerns and how poor clerics are. If the will not cooperate, find another group or solo. Maybe if we all just keep telling ppl that we deserve loot too, ppl will get the message. My friend today recommended if they say you shouldn't loot cuz you're a cleric, just do straight melee for a while and don't heal. If they complain, tell them "healing makes me not get to loot, so take your pick... I loot or you die"! He is a little rough with his approach though, so it's really up to you individually. I hope all looks up for all of us clerics. Thanks for reading this long grueling post!  :o)<br><br>Laterz!<br>Orchyd<br>9th Gnome Cleric<br>(Ittie Bittie Brigade)<br>Brell Serilis<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
