	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am level 48 dwarven cleric..I have grouped with the same people since I was level 14 most of the time.  Yes there are some people who don't think clerics should loot.  All I can say is, don't group with them.  At higher levels when you get your symbol spells, the tanks always make sure that you get to loot first for the bulk of the coin, or they make sure that you get decent cash items.  Trust me, at higher levels anyway, the tanks know how much you need cash.  As a dwarf with a low charisma, I pay over 11pp for a peridot, which you need to cast your higher level symbols.  I am luckily enough to have a bard in my group (high charisma) that sells my cash items for me, and buys my peridots:)  Sorry for the rambling.  Good Luck you guys in getting your cash!<br><br><br><br>Phalia Kordain &lt;Wolves of War&gt;<br>48 Cleric Xegony<br>*Proud to be a Wolf*<br>48 Cleric<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
