<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99494423568632></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99494423568632><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=7&mid=99494423568632>RE: best clerics</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jul 12th 9:23 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well again we have some truth with some fiction.<br><br>Wisdom is not GOD, in fact at lvl 37 I have already reached 200 WIS and have started swapping in +Mana stuff.  It is increadably easy to hit 200 WIS as a Cleric, and YES +MANA stuff is important, but there reeal factor during high level raids is not getting agro's and surviving when it happens anyway.  My Cleric is my secondary, so yes I do know the high end game.<br><br>What stats are most important?  Wisdom, not as long it is in the 180+ range (that's plenty of mana +lvl 50)  +Mana, again if you have some it's good, but you will see Cleric Buffs, Bard Songs and Nerco Mana Pumps will ensure you have enough mana all the time (but seldom full mana)<br><br>AC here we go, when that very nasty MOB turns on you, you're AC better be high enough to survive about 3 rounds of attacks.  It often takes that long for the tanks to taunt it off.  If your AC is lower than about 800 at level 50 you will die.  Defense skill is a factor here, so keep getting hit when you can to keep that skill near max.  The other factor here is AGILITY!!  so if you want to argue about UBER Cleric race, maybe it is that furry footed midget (halflings) since they will get hit much less than any other Cleric.<br><br>RESISTANCE!!!!  here is where you live or die during raids.  Can we say Dragon Fear, how about Trakanon's AE Poison.  Reststance gear is what keeps you alive, weather you get agro'd or not.  My Shadow Knight loses about 100 AC before a raid, when he switches in his resistance gear.  <br><br>So yes Wisdom is important, but not everything.  Yes AC is important and more important that WIS.  But when you want to survive the high end, you will want resistance gear over anything else.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
