	   <tr><td colspan=2>Okay, i'm gonna say it anyway. you picked the wrong class to solo at all with.<br><br>Okay, that's oughta the way. Now for what you wanted to hear.<br><br>Your screwed... the west antonica coast is not solo cleric happy. But if you come to the east coast it isn't so bad. As a good cleric (you sound erudite) Befallen up top is soloable by you if your careful and always know the exit route.<br><br>I myself solo'd as a cleric from 13 to 19 in lavastorm, outside the najena entrance... the catch? when i did it was before the ghoulbane quest change so i could run into najena to zone to safety... now you have to time it because if you run to najena their might be a pair of 25ish skele's waiting. Also for you you have to run the Nek forest... home of my race, and to be honest, we only like erudites if they're necros and sks.<br><br>now how to decide for yourself if you can solo a zone<br><br>two key things to ask yourself, and why you shouldn't have needed to post here... Are their undead there? Are their summoned creatures there?<br><br>If yes on one you can likely solo it if you know the zone geography. If yes on two then you MIGHT be able to... but be safe.<br><br>And DO NOT skimp on armor. When soloing as a cleric weapon is no big deal, your spells ar eyour big firepower, but AC is GOD. I wore a full small bronze suit when i solo'd lavastorm.<br><br>Well thats about it. both specific and generic advice on how to solo your cleric into the 20's. After that if you still want to solo your a fool... but a brave one and i help brave folks so let me give you a hint.<br><br>To solo as a cleric past 20 go to South Ro, Oasis, or LOIO... lots of ice and fire and war bone skele's. If it cons blue and your at full mana and have your evoc maxed you will win. Black you will likely win too. I didn't solo those levels, but a few times when i had a group i'd take them on one on one and i'd win with no help from my group so it could be done.<br><br>Think thats it. Good luck and good hunting.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
