<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99450798026895></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99450798026895><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=7&mid=99450798026895>Tactics & AC advice</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Jul 7th 8:13 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just wanted to say that I am a 35th dwarf cleric and have discovered a wonderful group or solo tactic for those that want to have fun as a semi-battle/tank cleric. Get a fairly fast 1hb weapon, and some descent armor - and be a dwarf (thick skin). In the level range 25-35 I was able to very effectively use the pattern nuke-stun-1hbash-1hbash-stun-1hbash-root-withdraw-med-med-heal-repeat_squence with small groups (preferabbly with a chanter/clarity/breeze and warrior) to get uber experience very rapidly and very few deaths. Its good to have 2 forms (later 3) of stun memmed up since they do take a while to recover between casts. I was actualy doing very effective 1hb to help the total meelee takedown on the mobs at a hit level that was effective but still below the warrior's damage to prevent the mob aggro on me. With this tactic I did take some flak from larger groups that wanted me to heal/buff only but many of the more experienceed in the group who saw what I was doing (and new my tactic) and know how efficient stun was on manna can convince the rest that you know what you are doing.<br><br>Also - as far as AC goes. "The best AC for a Cleric is a fully buffed and healed tank(s) and the knowledge of knowing not how to aggro the mob". This is the single biggest truth for a cleric. Explain to your group that you will heal them late in the battle (after a root) and to have faith that you wont let them die. Late heals scare many tanks but if they have confidence in you it all goes smoothly and you don't draw the aggro. Its even better if you have team with two clerics and a couple tanks and you each take responsibility for a single tank's buffs/heals. When possible defer heals till the mob is rooted or after battle.<br><br>Also, when up against undead casters and in a group - nuke-nuke-nuke as fast as you can and then stun/root and med if you dont kill them outright. This will preserve your tanks and you wont even have to heal them since the undead go down so fast.<br><br>Good Luck<br>Painbane - 35th Cleric (7th Hammer)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
